stories.storyText:
[Code Name] FEater 
[Gender] Female 
[Performance Experience] 11 years 
[Place of Birth] Yan 
[Date of Birth] Aug. 10 
[Race] Ursus 
[Height] 160cm 
[Infection Status] 
Infection confirmed by medical report.

[Physical Strength] Excellent
[Mobility] Normal
[Physical Resilience] Normal
[Tactical Acumen] Normal
[Combat Skill] Excellent
[Originium Arts Assimilation] Normal
A famous action movie star from Yan, FEater was forced to give up her film career after contracting Oripathy. She found a new purpose in life at Rhodes Island.

Imaging tests for this Operator showed blurry outlines of internal organs with visible dark spots. Unusually high concentrations of Originium particles were present in her circulatory system, indicating infection and confirming her as Infected at this stage.

[Cell-Originium Assimilation] 7.2% 
Visible traces of Originium on the subject's right leg, but it has not yet crystallized. 

[Blood Originium-Crystal Density] 0.21u/L 
FEater's infection is still in early stages and has yet to substantially impact her health.

FEater studied martial arts for many years prior to entering the film industry. She is the heir to the Tie Yi Liu He Quan, the Universal Fist of the Iron Will, one of Yan's great martial arts traditions. FEater has mastered all Five Elements, Eight Strikes, and Twelve Forms of her art, giving her the ability to deal devastating blows in the blink of an eye.

After contracting Oripathy, FEater's acting career and aspirations came to a screeching halt. But she didn't give into depression like one might expect, since movies to her were just one vehicle for delivering righteousness. The optimistic former star quickly landed back on her feet.

Even after becoming a movie star, even having been a legendary martial arts master, FEater has always been someone very approachable. In fact, she is actually rather naive and gets along easily with other Operators. Her hobbies include movies, of course, as well as Yan food, and chugging alcohol with a friendly crowd.

skins.description:
An outfit commonly worn by Operators.
While not as practical as a uniform, it's what they find most comfortable.

An outfit that has been improved after the Operator's Promotion.
Custom-made to suit each Operator's experiences and needs, these outfits are designed to provide them maximum flexibility on any battlefield. Furthermore, this is all done without compromising the comfort that they've come to expect.
<color name=#ffffff>0011 New Release / Gourmet. FEater's outfit from a bestselling Lungmen foodie film. Incorporates a sporty inner layer and a traditional knotted jacked, once all the rage.</color>

MARTHE Sports Line. A limited-edition outfit commemorating FEater's 3rd Anniversary of setting the box office record. Lightweight, breathable, and comfortably-fitting. However, anyone who knows FEater also knows that she has never worn this outfit properly.

modules.desc:
Operator FEater has demonstrated a remarkable aptitude for physically distancing the enemy via applied force so as to preserve the front.
The Field Operations Department has thus passed the following resolution:
This operator shall be appointed a Specialist Operator during field operations to exercise Push Stroker responsibilities.
In witness whereof,
This badge is hereby conferred upon the above named.

'Ah-choo... ah-choo...' Outside the kitchen door, everyone is wiping their noses, sneezing one after another like there's no tomorrow, even their eyes sealed shut. The culprit: a pungent, choking aroma wafting from a crack in the door, inflaming everyone's nostrils, tickling their throats. 'Ah-choo... ah-choo...' Despite how unbearable it is, nobody's willing to take even one step away. People are still flowing into the cafeteria, in fact. 'Is—Is it ready? Is FEater still inside?' '*cough* *cough*... Yeah, you can hear the banging. She's probably still chopping chilis.' 'So spicy... I—I'm almost at my limit... ah-choo!' 'Then you'd better get out of here... *cough* *cough*...' 'No way am I letting you jump my spot... ah-choo!' With a 'crrrk,' the kitchen door swings open, and in an instant, the entire room is filled with a scent rich and stimulating. Right behind it comes FEater carrying a plate, her smile brimming with satisfaction. 'It's done! Step on up and try it, guys. I've even added my hometown chili paste for a special touch.' Seeing the brilliant red pepper slices and vividly shining chili oil, the crowd craning to steal a look just a moment before is now hush-silent. They share looks of alarm at each other, each sporting their own unique expression. 'Don't let it scare you! Sit down and try!' 'I assume... it's going to be very spicy, FEater?' 'Nope, not spicy at all. I just tasted it.' 'Then I suppose I will.' No sooner do the words come out than the crowd parts perfectly into two, and under the admiring attention of all, one lone operator walks up to the table, rubs her hands, and picks up a pair of chopsticks with a tremble. 'Come on, try!' As if unable to withstand FEater's expectant gaze, the operator's chopsticks chatter like teeth, with a sharp clack-clack-clack-clack. Finally, after circling above the plate a few times, they descend, carefully picking up a piece of meat not totally stuffed with peppers. She lifts the chopsticks high and gives them a shake, then two, hoping the chili seeds and peppercorns will fall out of the roll of meat, and right away senses it still won't be enough, leading her to wipe it a few times against the edge of the plate. Only once it's wiped bare of all excess oil does she finally take a deep breath, and prepare to put it in her mouth. 'Wait, give it a rinse in your glass!' The prompting voice from the crowd enters her ears, and she sees the light. Her chopsticks make an about face and dunk the meat in her drinking glass, and instantly, what was clear warm water is now scarlet throughout, beads of oil floating about within. The sight of the meat's original, fair color greets her. The operator sighs with palpable relief, and scarfs it down in one clean go. 'How is it? Good?' asks FEater with a wink. '*cough* *cough* *cough* *cough*... Wh—Where's my water? *cough* *cough*—' '*glug* *glug*...' 'Hey, isn't that the water she just...' 'Pppffffhh—!'

voice_lines.voiceText: So... I have to just stand here and not do anything? Laaaame.
These gauntlets aren't that heavy. See? Even a dainty little girl like me can carry 'em around real easy.
You remember fighting by my side before? Can't say I remember fighting by yours, sorry... I just fight for what's right, that's all.

Hah. That boxer, Beehunter? She's really something! I enjoyed sparring with her so much, I had to throw out some serious moves. And she's got an amazing honey collection too. Wanna visit her with me next time? You gotta learn some kung fu first, though.

Reading a movie magazine...? Well, guess what? The 'hot kung-fu actress' mentioned in this article is ME! What? You don't believe me? Come on, look! This is me, can't you tell? C'mon, that's definitely me!
Do I regret forgoing my previous life? Well, sometimes, of course. But the world ain't kind to us Infected. Lots of places I'm not allowed to go. It blows.
There's a street full of food stalls in the neighboring city. And... a candy shop over there? And a theme park? Aww, Doctor, can I get a day off? I wanna check out these places!

Am I satisfied with life at Rhodes Island, you ask? Hm, to be honest... It's even sweeter than what they show in the movies! I got cool opponents to practice with, top-notch food, and by working here, I'm doing something good for the world! What could be better!

Doctor, look! What do you think about this script? Oh, who's gonna act in it, you wonder? You and I are gonna be the main characters! There's this scene where we leap from the roof of a thirty-story building and slide all the way down. Isn't that cool? Hey! Come back! Wait!
You're catching some z's, eh? Guess I'll slack off for a bit too. Man, this couch is so fluffy!
You swear you've seen my face before? Probably saw it in a movie I was in! Call me FEater, and what I do from here is your call!
It's over? Come on, let's watch just a while longer. We're almost at the fun part!
Oooh! A promotion! Thanks so much, Doctor!
This here's the perfect opportunity to show you some REAL kung fu!
All right, it's show time!
Huh? I'm the leader? Not sure how it'll go, but...
This is gonna be exciting!
I'm FEater. Pleased to beat you!
Un-huh.
Here we go!
All right!
Show time!
HI-YAH!
This is straight out of one of my movies!
From flexibility comes power!
Who says a movie star couldn't be a real kung-fu master!
Wow, it's over?
It's over already? I was just starting to get warmed up.
Hey, it's no biggie. Just a few scratches and bruises.
Aw... I just wanna go home and sleep...
Now that's stylin'!
Stop that, I'm getting dizzy!
Hey, Doctor, want my autograph? I'll take a pic with you if you want, too!
Arknights.

Happy New Year, Doctor! Hehe, back in the old days, theaters would screen my movies this time every year, all playing to a full house!  Still, can't live in the past forever. I gotta punch ahead, and people gotta move on forward. Let's forget all our grievances for today!
Did you have breakfast yet, Doctor?

Doctor, happy birthday! There's this saying that 'life's a movie you can't reshoot,' so when it comes to a key scene, you've gotta live life like you're on fire! Any birthday wishes, Doctor? Gimme a wish as cool as the lead of an action movie, and I'll help you make it come true!

After I became an Infected, I thought for a bit that my career and my life were both over. Rhodes didn't just rein in my illness, but also gave me a fresh start. Standing up again in dire straits is exactly what the hero does, right? Doctor, Let's climb back to the top, together!
